org.jgrapht.graph.specifics

Class UndirectedSpecifics<V,E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jgrapht.graph.specifics.UndirectedSpecifics<V,E>
  • Type Parameters:
    V - the graph vertex type
    E - the graph edge type
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Specifics<V,E>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    FastLookupUndirectedSpecifics

    public class UndirectedSpecifics<V,E>
extends Object
implements Specifics<V,E>, Serializable
    Plain implementation of UndirectedSpecifics. This implementation requires the least amount of memory, at the expense of slow edge retrievals. Methods which depend on edge retrievals, e.g. getEdge(V u, V v), containsEdge(V u, V v), addEdge(V u, V v), etc may be relatively slow when the average degree of a vertex is high (dense graphs). For a fast implementation, use FastLookupUndirectedSpecifics.
    Author:
    Barak Naveh, Joris Kinable
    See Also:
    Serialized Form
